### Missing Endpoints Now Documented
- **Credentials Management** (12 endpoints) - Create, assign, revoke test credentials
- **Credential Inquiries** (6 endpoints) - Hacker credential requests
- **Incremental Activities** (2 endpoints) - **Critical for efficient sync**
- **Report Intents AI** (9 endpoints) - AI-assisted vulnerability drafting
- **Analytics** (1 endpoint) - Time-series metrics
- **Email** (1 endpoint) - Markdown emails to org members
- **HAI AI** (2+ endpoints) - AI chat with report context
- **Hacker Financial** (3 endpoints) - Balance, earnings, payouts
- **Hacktivity** (1 endpoint) - Public vulnerability feed
- **Asset Management** (3+ endpoints) - Tagging, scope updates
- **Messaging** (2 endpoints) - Message hackers, external platforms

### 2024-2025 API Timeline Documented
- **March 2024:** Hacktivity API for hackers
- **May 2024:** Asset Tagging with API support
- **August 2024:** Delete sensitive attachments via API
- **September 2024:** Report Intents API (AI-assisted drafting)
- **December 2024-2025:** Asset tag creation, get all categories
- **January 2025:** CVSS 4.0 support, Email endpoint
- **July 2025:** Message hackers endpoint
- **October 2025:** Notify external platforms, update asset scope

### Key Research Findings
- ✅ No API v2 exists - HackerOne evolves v1 with backward compatibility
- ✅ No GraphQL API - REST only
- ✅ Webhooks require Professional tier (as of January 2025)
- ✅ Incremental activities endpoint is critical for production (10-100x more efficient)
- ✅ Rate limits updated October 2023 (report pages: 600→300 req/min)
- ✅ CVSS 4.0 support added January 2025 (backward compatible with 3.1)

